    "name": {
      "zh": "Zastava M76 7.92x57毫米狙击步枪",
      "en": "Zastava M76 7.92x57 marksman rifle"
    },
    "shortName": {
      "zh": "M76",
      "en": "M76"
    },
    "description": {
      "zh": "Zastava M76是一款由Zastava武器公司研发制造的军用半自动精确射手步枪。该枪于20世纪70年代中期问世，随后成为塞尔维亚军队及其前身南斯拉夫人民军（JNA）的制式精确射手步枪。其设计初衷与苏联德拉贡诺夫SVD相同，旨在为步兵排提供精确火力支援能力。",
      "en": "The Zastava M76 is a military semi-automatic designated marksman rifle developed and manufactured by Zastava Arms. The Zastava Arms Company released the M76 in the mid-1970s. Since then it became the standard issue designated marksman rifle in the Serbian army and its predecessor the Yugoslav People's Army (JNA). It was designed to fulfill the same role as the Soviet Dragunov SVD, which was to provide a designated marksman capability to the infantry platoon."
    },
